---
title: "Anatomy of a Bolus"
---
flowchart LR
    Bolus["<b>Bolus</b><br/> insulin, programmed, delivered bolusType, kind, automatic duration, unabsorbed timestamp, deviceId<br/><br/><i>FKs:</i> bolusCalculationId? apsSnapshotId? deviceId? correlationId?<br/><br/><i>embedded:</i> insulinContext?"]

    subgraph recommendation["1. Recommendation (what was suggested)"]
        direction TB
        BolusCalculation["<b>BolusCalculation</b><br/> bgInput, carbInput, IOB insulinRecommendation carbRatio, calculationType splitNow / splitExt, preBolus"]
        rWhy["<b>Why separate?</b><br/>A wizard run can produce 0, 1, or N boluses (user adjusts and splits). The inputs and the delivered dose have independent lifecycles -- you might keep the calculation for audit even if no bolus was delivered."]
    end

    subgraph snapshot["2. Pharmacokinetic Snapshot (what was true at delivery)"]
        direction TB
        TreatmentInsulinContext["<b>TreatmentInsulinContext</b><br/>(embedded value object)<br/><br/>patientInsulinId insulinName dia, peak, curve concentration"]
        PatientInsulin["<b>PatientInsulin</b><br/>(live, mutable)<br/><br/>name, role, formulationId dia, peak, curve, concentration isCurrent, isPrimary"]
        sWhy["<b>Why snapshot, not FK?</b><br/>If we only stored a FK to PatientInsulin, editing today's DIA would silently rewrite every historical IOB curve. Freezing the parameters at delivery keeps history stable and audits honest."]
    end

    subgraph trigger["3. Algorithm Trigger (who decided)"]
        direction TB
        ApsSnapshot["<b>ApsSnapshot</b><br/> aidAlgorithm iob, cob, currentBg, eventualBg recommendedBolus, enacted predictedDefaultJson, ..."]
        tWhy["<b>Why FK, not duplicate?</b><br/>A single APS cycle can enact a temp basal AND an SMB. Both the Bolus and the TempBasal point back to the same ApsSnapshot, so 'what was the algorithm thinking?' has one answer per cycle, not N copies."]
    end

    subgraph hardware["4. Physical Delivery (what actually delivered)"]
        direction TB
        Device["<b>Device</b><br/>(auto-discovered)<br/><br/>category, type, serial firstSeen / lastSeen"]
        hWhy["<b>Why FK to Device?</b><br/>The pump that delivered this dose may not be the patient's current pump. Pinning the physical unit lets us trace 'which Omnipod pod was that?' even after the patient swaps hardware."]
    end

    subgraph sibling["5. Legacy Sibling Link (carbs that came with it)"]
        direction TB
        CarbIntake["<b>CarbIntake</b><br/> carbs, carbTime absorptionTime"]
        cWhy["<b>Why correlationId, not FK?</b><br/>A legacy v1 'Meal Bolus' treatment carries both insulin and carbs in one row. We split them so each can be queried, edited, and aggregated alone -- but a shared correlationId still says 'these belong together' (see MealEvent)."]
    end

    BolusCalculation -- "bolusCalculationId" --> Bolus
    PatientInsulin -- "captured at delivery time" --> TreatmentInsulinContext
    TreatmentInsulinContext -. embedded in .-> Bolus
    ApsSnapshot -- "apsSnapshotId" --> Bolus
    Device -- "deviceId" --> Bolus
    CarbIntake -. correlationId .- Bolus

    BolusCalculation -.- rWhy
    TreatmentInsulinContext -.- sWhy
    ApsSnapshot -.- tWhy
    Device -.- hWhy
    CarbIntake -.- cWhy

    classDef center fill:#fef3c7,stroke:#b45309,color:#7c2d12,stroke-width:3px
    classDef record fill:#fff,stroke:#475569,color:#0f172a
    classDef live fill:#ecfccb,stroke:#4d7c0f,color:#365314
    classDef snap fill:#fee2e2,stroke:#b91c1c,color:#7f1d1d
    classDef why fill:#f3e8ff,stroke:#7e22ce,color:#581c87,font-style:italic

    class Bolus center
    class BolusCalculation,ApsSnapshot,Device,CarbIntake record
    class PatientInsulin live
    class TreatmentInsulinContext snap
    class rWhy,sWhy,tWhy,hWhy,cWhy why
